stylometry: Transportation is moving something from point A to point B across an arc, or pathway.  A flow is the product that is being moved. Transshipment problems involve shipping to and from various areas, but some can both ship and receive, which makes them more complicated problems.  Nodes are the ways we ship them to various areas.  Ex problem) If you have different stepts to manufacturing a product, different factories are responsible for adding onto them.  The factories can receive the product and ship it to another factory, or warehouse, when they finish their part.
